3.title: Gourmet Good & Evil
3.plot: James checks out the Inventing Room in Denver, which dishes up frozen desserts made with liquid nitrogen. He also samples sliders with innovative toppings at the Burnt Truck in Irvine, California; alligator tacos at the Taco de Paco truck in Baton Rouge, Louisiana; and gourmet hot dogs at Austin's Evil Wiener truck.

4.title: Lip Smackin' Delights
4.plot: Jen-N-Outlaw's Fish Fry Truck has Alabama-style crawfish in Brooklyn. Also: Caribbean cuisine from Riff's Truck in Nashville; Asian-Latin fusion tacos from Dos Chinos truck in Irvine, Cal.; and mini donuts from Denver's Sugar Lips truck.

5.title: Rib-Tastic!
5.plot: Massive portions of barbecue ribs are dished up at MOgridder's BBQ in the Bronx. The host also samples crepes from Go-Ya-Ya's truck in Baton Rouge, Louisiana; Asian-inspired eats at Austin, Texas' East Side King trailer; and classic burgers and shakes from the 1950s-style Barbie Burgers truck in Nashville.

7.title: Cordon Bleu, Street Style
7.plot: Stops include "Fukuburger" in Las Vegas for Japanese-inspired burgers; "Soul Patrol" in Honolulu for Southern fried chicken; Orlando's "Big Wheel Provisions" for beef-heart skewers and deviled eggs with roasted peppers.

8.title: Hawaii-Thai-Oh
8.plot: James samples Japanese cuisine with a Mexican twist at the "Jogasaki Burrito" truck in Los Angeles. Also spotlighted: the "Opal Thai" truck in Honolulu; "Sloppi Jo's Roving Eatery" in Las Vegas; and "2 Fat 2 Fly" truck in South Carolina.

9.title: Yum Yum
9.plot: James checks out Rosa's Bella Cucina, a mobile Italian deli, in Burbank, Cal. He also visits the Yum Yum Cupcake Truck in Orlando, & samples dim sum from the Tasty Bunz truck in Las Vegas, & fish tacos from Camille's on Wheels in Honolulu.

10.title: The Smokin' South
10.plot: Smoked meats are sampled at South Carolina's "Bone-in Artisan Barbecue on Wheels". The host also tastes French-Asian fusion cuisine at the "Dim-Sum-a-Go-Go" truck in Miami, and Filipino fusion food at the "Flip't Out Eats" truck in Hawaii.

11.title: Miami Nice
11.plot: Sampled: Venezuelan comfort food from the "Mr. Good Stuff" truck in Miami; Philly cheese-steaks from the "Food Slingers" truck in Las Vegas; Filipino rice plates from the "Wow Silog Truck" in San Jose.

12.title: 'Gator Time
12.plot: "Swamp Shack" in Portland, Oregon, serves up homemade bread pudding and alligator jambalaya. Also spotlighted: "Latin Burger and Taco Truck" in Miami; "Shrimp Pimp Truck" in Santa Monica, Cal.; and "Strada Cucina" in Charleston, S.C.

13.title: Sounds Tasty
13.plot: Fresh Cuban cuisine is sampled at the Babaloo Truck in San Francisco. Also featured: San Francisco's Brass Knuckle Truck; the Dog House in Portland, Oregon.

1.plot: The "Caplansky Deli Truck" in Ontario is spotlighted. Also: the "Lake Street Creamery", a mobile ice-cream parlor in Los Angeles; "Gourdough", a donut shop housed in a vintage Airstream trailer in Austin.

2.title: Global Gastronomy
2.plot: Top Chef Canada (2011) alum Connie DeSousa dishes up gourmet hamburgers from her "Alley Burger" truck in Calcary. Also visited: the "Everybody Love Love Jhal Muri Express" food cart in London; the "Wicked Witches" truck in Tampa Bay, Florida; and the "Dim and Den Sum" truck in Cleveland.

5.plot: Sweet and savory pies are sampled at Dangerously Delicious Pies in Washington, D.C. Also visited: the Fries and Dolls truck in Calary; Papa Pemone's truck in New York City; and the La Gusguita truck in Tampa, Florida.

2.plot: Street food from San Francisco, Maine and Houston.

3.title: Music to Your Mouth
3.plot: Breakfast at the "Fried Egg I'm in Love" in Portland, Oregon; and Chinese takeout from the "Rice Box" in Houston. Also: "3-Sum Eats" in San Francisco; and "Wrapper's Delight" in Nashville.

4.plot: A trip to Houston includes Vietnamese food from "Phamily Bites" and a diverse menu offered at the "Modular". Also: San Francisco's "Bacon Bacon"; and an Indianapolis truck that specializes in macaroni and cheese.

5.plot: Hawaiian fare from "808 Grinds" in Portland, Oregon, is featured, along with fish dishes served up at "St. John's Fire" in Houston. Also: artisan pizzas in Louisville; and make-from-scratch food in Indianapolis.

6.title: Some of This, Some of That
6.plot: Cajun fare in Indianapolis; Indian-inspired cuisine at Miami's "Gypsy Kitchen"; gourmet food served on a stick in Houston; and a Louisville truck that specializes in grilled cheese.
